text: Tamparuli is one of the districts in Sabah. The most iconic symbol of Tamparuli is Tamparuli Bridge or Jambatan Tamparuli. The Tamparuli Suspension Bridge became even more iconic after the creation of the "Tamparuli Bridge Song" by the Justin Lusah. Tamparuli is also known for its local culture and is a gateway for visitors heading to the highlands, such as the popular Kundasang area and Mount Kinabalu. == References == Category:Settlements in Malaysia
